Content: Northwestern has a tough draw in taking on Purdue and Michigan State twice in 2023-24... But where do those matchups rank among all of the team’s games? We asked our staff to break it down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We begin our preview of Northwestern basketball with four under-the-radar contributors for Joe McKeown, including two first-years.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern volleyball displayed its tenacity against the Wolverines and Spartans up in Michigan.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kate Drohan is here to stay.

Name: Inside NU
Content: As it hits its bye, Northwestern football could actually make a bowl game — although the Wildcats will need to notch two or three more wins against Big Ten play, including some top opponents.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern has a tough draw in taking on Purdue and Michigan State twice in 2023-24... But where do those matchups rank among all of the team’s games? We asked our staff to break it down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern women’s golf recorded its second-straight top-three finish of the fall, placing third overall at the Illini Invitational.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The reigning Big Ten Coach of the Year will be in Evanston for the foreseeable future.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
After hours of deliberation across three meetings, the Evanston Land Use Commission finally voted Wednesday night.

The Commission approved of Northwestern’s Ryan Field proposal but, crucially, did not endorse rezoning for concerts.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A bye week and better health brought new opportunities for some former ‘Cats:

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats have already exceeded expectations. Why not enjoy it?

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern men’s soccer currently: 

- Is the highest ranked Big Ten team 
- Sits atop the Big Ten standings 
- Is one of just seven unbeaten teams remaining in the country 

Here’s how they’ve fared recently (SPOILER: They’re doing pretty well):

Name: Inside NU
Content: Who’s up, who’s down halfway into the CFB season?

Name: Inside NU
Content: With this, we'd like to invite everyone to participate in our midseason/BYE WEEK MAILBAG!Comment to ask us anything within reason, Northwestern sports-related (so much going on right now) or not. We'll answer a bunch of them in a mailbag that should go up in a few days.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Who did it better?

Name: Inside NU
Content: A leadership update from us:  will be joining  and  as Co-EICs of the site. This, of course, can only make for an even more fun Twitter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It’s getting colder outside, and that means one thing: basketball is near.

Name: Inside NU
Content: No one predicted the ‘Cats would be .500 by this point.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
No. 1 Northwestern Wildcats has a nice ring to it.

We've heard it not too long ago, and we're hearing it again today: the 'Cats are at the top of the  national poll.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern field hockey’s resounding win over No. 3 Iowa makes it the favorite to win its first outright Big Ten regular season title in nearly 30 years.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And the Oscar for Best Motion Picture of 2023 goes to...

Name: Inside NU
Content: At the rough halfway point of the college football season,  hands out (some real, some arbitrary) awards for the Big Ten this week

Name: Inside NU
Content: With only a handful of opportunities left, Northwestern needs to find its stride soon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With the bye week, Northwestern has the chance to dig into the tape and right some wrongs before the second half of the season commences. Here are five things we learned from Northwestern’s 23-20 victory over Howard.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Kirtz on the new Drake album:

"I was defintely streaming it when it came out on Friday." 

On his favorite song from the album:

"The one with Yeat."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller on Eden James' performance:

"We gotta keep our leverage to stop those big plays."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller on his safety: 

"That was the first safety of my career."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Kirtz on having Sullivan at QB:

"I know what he can do...I like Brendan a lot."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Xander Mueller and Bryce Kirtz now taking questions.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan on being sacked four times today:

"A few of them were definitely on me...Definitely got to take a look in the mirror after this game."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan on Ben Bryant today:

"Ben did a great job on the sideline. He was the number one supporter."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan on finding out Ben Bryant was a game-time decision:

"I'm going to prepare every week like I'm a starter."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brendan Sullivan and Cam Johnson now taking questions.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on student section filling up today:

"I want to continue to express our gratitude for that group."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on "Trust Yourself" sign that players slap in locker room:

"At the end of the day, we need to trust our teammates, have a sense of belief."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Ben Bryant and AJ Henning's availability for Nebraska:

"We do expect both those guys to be available."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun in primary focus of bye week:

"As a staff, we'll put Howard to bed tomorrow morning and start Nebraska prep."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On Howard outgaining NU in total yardage:

"The biggest mistakes I've made...is getting tied up in the yardage battle."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On Sullivan's leadership:

"He understands it requires every single guy in that locker room."

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun on the last drive: "What a great way to instill confidence in our team that we can close out games."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on going for it on 4th down late in the game:

"We really felt like wind was going to be a factor today."

Name: Inside NU
Content: It was closer than expected, but Northwestern came out on top.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern staved off a late-game rally by Howard to get back to .500 on the season.

Name: Inside NU
Content: FINAL: Northwestern 23, Howard 20

Name: Inside NU
Content:
That'll be game. In what never should've been a nail-biter, it took some impressive runs in the final two minutes to secure NU the victory.

The 'Cats advance to a 0.500 record, moving to 3-3 on the year.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Woah. 

Tyus runs for a first down, a flag is thrown, then the ref picks up the flag and says there's no holding on the play.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard attempts the onside kick, and Rod Heard juggles it before corralling it.

NU has the ball on the Howard 43, and if we've learned anything from Braun this quarter, it's that field goals aren't an option unless the 'Cats are inside the HU25.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern led by 16 less than five minutes (of game time) ago.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard just scored a touchdown. Wow.

23-20, NU leads with 2:32 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
No stop was acquired.

First down Howard inside the redzone.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 3rd-and-1 incoming for Howard. Obviously four-down territory, but a stop would be great.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Williams completes a screen to James on 3rd-and-long, who takes it all the way to the NU 38.

Anxiety  setting in.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams overthrows his receiver by just a yard or two. Would've been a massive gain for the Bison.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
So Northwestern punts with about six minutes left to play.

The 'Cats lead by 10, but Howard has shown a little life in the second half.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
That fourth down call from Braun up 16 with under 10 minutes to go is looking more and more questionable.

In all likelihood, the outcome of the game won't change because of it, but it's still odd.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Eden James just ran the ball back for a 64-yard touchdown to open the drive. Wow.

NU leads, 23-13, after a failed two-point attempt from Howard.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Andddddd Sullivan is sacked for a big loss, giving Howard the ball at its own 36.

A questionable call there from Braun.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Offense is trotting back out.

Braun wants the killshot it seems.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On 3rd-and-12, Sullivan scrambles for nine.

Braun kept the offense out there and just called a timeout. Not sure about the logic?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan tries a 35-yard shot to the endzone for Cam Johnson, but it's broken up by a Howard defender.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Weird sequence: back-to-back penalties.

The first was on a Howard defender for unsportsmanlike conduct who chucked his mouthpiece  after the last play.

Then a snap infraction by an NU lineman.

Net gain of 10 yards for the 'Cats.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Anthony Tyus snags a 12-yard pickup to earn NU a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson hauls in a catch that's good for a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Gain of two yards on first from Tyus, and Sullivan follows it up with a dart to Johnson for 11.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Big pick up by Anthony Tyus is called back on a holding call. 

1st-and-20.

Name: Inside NU
Content: This game has me ALIVE AND WELL

Name: Inside NU
Content: https://x.com/seahawksfan314/status/1710767816456945826?s=46&t=F6mk-SrfptAXgiaEw0AJgg…

Name: Inside NU
Content: (my esteemed colleague  just asked me why I'm tweeting in all-caps in a 16-point game in the fourth quarter...have you ever heard of passion, patrick?)

Name: Inside NU
Content:
AHHHHHHHHHHHHHH MORE PRESSURE AND THE DEFENSE LAYS OUT WILLIAMS 

'CATS' BALL

Name: Inside NU
Content: CLUTCH SACK FROM RICHIE HAGARTY TO FORCE 4TH-AND-FOREVER

Name: Inside NU
Content: Time for a Northwestern Redzone Stand

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Facing pressure while scrambling, Williams lofts a short pass to a receiver in the endzone and puts a little too much oomph on it. 

A close call that now brings up 3rd-and-7.

Name: Inside NU
Content: James rushes to the NU 9 for a gain of three.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams and Ilarranza connect for five, and the Bison get the first down they were looking for.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams gets it to Ilarranza for six yards, stopping Howard two short of the first — the Bison will go for it.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The third quarter ends with a Jarett Hunter 2-yard run.

Heading into the final period, the 'Cats lead by 16 but Howard is driving.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams and Hawthorne have a miscommunication on first down, as the QB sends a pass to nobody close to the endzone while the WR was near the 20-yard line.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Not sure what I just watched.

Eden James looked like he was about to get stuffed and turned it into a zig-zagging 26-yard pickup...*sigh*

Howard now at NU 25.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The Bison go with three straight runs with Eden James and get the first down.

Howard is sitting at midfield right now. Touchdown here is almost necessary to stay in this game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Howard picks up a first down to open its drive via a 14-yard pass.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Me pulling up to this Brendan Sullivan clinic

Name: Inside NU
Content: All I'm saying is that the TD pass came on the first actual play out of the break...#KeepHimOnTheDanceCam

Name: Inside NU
Content:
That touchdown pass was super impressive — Sullivan on the run, Johnson streaking down the sideline, and the QB puts it right in the bread basket.

NU extends it lead, 23-7.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
DOT DOT DOT 

SULLIVAN SLINGS ONE TO CAM JOHNSON FOR A HUGE TOUCHDOWN. A THING OF BEAUTY.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
An Odell-esque catch by Cam Johnson that would've led to a first down will get negated because of an ineligible man downfield.

Sullivan held on to the ball too long there, which led to the flag.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Guy in the Purple Pride shirt on the dance-cam right now is electrifying this crowd.

Touchdown incoming.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Porter stuffed near the line — gets two. 

Bajakian is definitely leaning into the run game on this drive.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan does it himself and picks up enough for a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Porter runs it again, and he picks up one. He's had a tough time finding any open holes today.

3rd-and-2 on Howard's 39.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After a 12-man penalty on Howard, Porter takes a run for two yards.

Name: Inside NU
Content: SUPER TOUGH CATCH FROM CAM JOHNSON ON THIRD DOWNHe moves the chains!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Cam Porter tries his hand now, and he rushes for six.

3rd-and-5 up next.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On NU's opening play of the drive, Sullivan hands it off to Himon. He loses 1 — 2nd-and-11 coming up.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
UPDATE: Student section holding pretty strong given we’re halfway through the 3rd. 

Not sure if a Northwestern score here would keep people around or empower them to head out.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Special teams continue to impress. 

Anthony Tyus returns the kickoff for 30 yards, and NU will start its drive at its own 42.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Touchdown Howard. 

The Bison use a different QB, Ja'Shawn Scroggins, who rushes it in for six. Not sure if the substitution is due to Williams being hurt from the last play.

16-7, Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Officials say no targeting. Howard's ball on NU 1.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
This goal-line stand has been super weird...

After the disconcerting signals penalty, Howard center snapped the ball high. Williams corralled it + tossed it in  vicinity of LOS to avoid incoming sack.

Now the officials are reviewing the play for a potential targeting call.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
RARE FLAG ALERT: Northwestern gets called for a "disconcerting signals" penalty — basically trying to make noise to mess up Howard's snap count.

Gives the Bison an automatic first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On 3rd-and-7, Williams finds Ilarraza, who darts up to the NU 1.

The original call was a TD, but the officials wiped that off the board. The Bison were also marked half a yard short of the first, so this will be fourth down.

Howard will go for it.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams takes a shot to the corner of the endzone and perfect coverage by Rod Heard keeps the Bison off the scoreboard (for now).

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Eden James rushes it for a 3-yard pickup.

Howard is inside the NU ten-yard line.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
'Cats defenders collapse the pocket on Williams, but the Howard QB finds an open receiver who squeaks out a first down. 

The Bison are now comfortably in the redzone.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On second down, Tony Bedell loses two yards on the run. Here comes 3rd-and-8.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard runs back-to-back plays up the middle of the Northwestern defense.

The first leads to a first down, and the second results in a 4-yard gain.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams find his receiver for a short pass, who turns up the sideline and gets nine.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
James nabs another 2-yard pickup, and the Bison get a new set of downs.

Howard is driving and is nearing the redzone.

Name: Inside NU
Content: James rushes for two on second down, which will bring up a 3rd-and-short.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams finds Ilarraza again, this time for seven.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams sails one over his receiver's head on first down, but redeems himself with a nice pass to Richie Ilarraza good for 17.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams finds Kasey Hawthorne for a first down. The WR had a big cushion of open space to make the easy catch.

Name: Inside NU
Content: James opens the second half with a 4-yard run for Howard.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We're back from the break, and Howard takes the kickoff to their own 26.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Me when the press box has actual food

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard’s marching band is on the field right now and has this crowd the loudest it’s been all day. 

This is talent.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard takes a knee to send it to halftime. 'Cats lead, 16-0.

Pretty cohesive first half from Brendan Sullivan, who is 8-for-11 w/ a rushing and passing TD. The Bison have gotten to Sullivan a LOT today, with tons of pressures and three sacks.

Defense has held up very well too.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Student section appears to be at capacity heading into halftime. About as good as you could ask for.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
With 26 seconds left in the half, Northwestern takes a much needed 16-0 lead.

Aside from the opening drive and safety — both in the first quarter — NU looked like it was stalling out a bit.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sources say Braun saw this tweet and laughed at the idea of running the ball.

Name: Inside NU
Content: TOUCHDOWN 'CATS!!!! SULLIVAN TO KIRTZ ON A FOUR-YARD SLANT!!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
SETTING THE SCENE:

- 31 seconds left in the half
- NU has one timeout left
- the 'Cats are on Howard's four-yard line

Would Braun try running it here, given how good the RBs have been on this drive? Or three straight endzone shots?

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Clock is dwindling as the half nears, and Sullivan finds Mangieri for five yards and a first down.

Mangieri had great awareness there to extend for the first down — probably got it by a few inches.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After Porter gets nothing on first down, the 'Cats try Sullivan's hand. He scrambles for four, bringing up 3rd-and-5.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Himon grabs another 10, good for another first down. 

NU now at the Bison's 14.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Himon gets 12 on first down, bursting through the middle of the line.

He's so quick in-person.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Cam Porter is taking over. 

Another set of back-to-back runs — the most recent one for 11 yards on 3rd-and-5.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The pocket collapses on Sullivan on first down and he's able to make it back to the LOS. No gain.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bajakian keeps it in Porter's hands for second and third down. The senior picks up the first.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Cam Porter rushes right for eight on first down.

Looked like he ran out of space to turn up the field, but if he could've, that would've gone for a lot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: 'Cats grab the first down with a nice six-yard pass to Johnson.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On first down, NU picks up eight on the ground — courtesy of Cam Johnson.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Eden James tried bouncing out on 4th-and-2 when he might've had a gap if he'd run straight up the middle.

Quinton Williams was yelling at his RB after the play for opting to swing outside.

NU takes over at its own 24.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NU GETS THE STOP ON FOURTH DOWN!!!!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Theran Johnson comes up with a textbook tackle and stops the Howard pass-catcher just short on third down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Wheeler picks up nothing on first down, and Eden gets four on second.

Now, a big third down awaits.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Williams finds a wide open receiver for a hefty pick up on third down.

Howard is driving and finds itself at NU's 28.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braylen Smith jukes multiple NU defenders and probably runs 20 yards laterally to pick up two. 

3rd-and-short up next.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On first down, Howard picks up four on the ground.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
After a review, officials determine Williams' deep pass to Kasey Hawthorne was complete. 

Gain of 21 puts the Bison in NU territory.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Never mind...statsheet has been updated to say Howard starts this drive at the 34. I try to add in some color and this is what I get.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard starts its drive at the 33-yard line after a 40-yarder from Renner.

Fun Fact: between both teams, three drives have started at the 33 today. Popular number.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan completes one to Himon for six yards, but NU needed nine. Here comes the punt team.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Correction: Howard made it to the NU 49 and then got called for a false start, pushing itself back into its own territory.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan makes a bad read on the RPO, and he tries to keep it. Gets nowhere. 

Third down on the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern takes over from its own 20-yard line, and Sullivan is forced to throw it away on first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Williams throws an incompletion on third down, and Howard will punt from its own 42. 

The Bison haven't crossed midfield all day.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A Bison false start makes it 3rd-and-6. Braun calls a timeout to reset the defense.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
James runs across the field to turn what looked like a no-gain into a seven-yard pickup.

James trucked two NU defenders, who both had trouble getting up after the play.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Williams take a shot on first down and it's just out of reach for the receiver, who wanted a PI.

The NU defender probably got away with a jersey pull there.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Howard picks up its second first down of the day thanks to an 11-yard rush from Eden James.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
NU takes an intentional delay of game to give Renner a chance at pinning the Bison. 

Doesn't seem to work, as Renner boots it 17 yards to the Howard 24.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Speaking of...Sullivan takes a sack on third down as he tries to scramble out of the pocket. Three sacks on the day for the Bison.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Some Q1 takeaways:

- Sullivan looks mostly comfortable passing, but he's facing pressure consistently from the Howard pass rush
- Defense has been elite, forcing a safety and allowing just one first down
- Special teams...

Name: Inside NU
Content:
End of the first quarter.

NU leads, 9-0.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Just like that, it's third down again. Shows you how fast this offense is moving.

Name: Inside NU
Content: SULLIVAN STEPS UP IN THE POCKET AND CONVERTS ON 3rd-AND-17 TO KIRTZ. BIG TIME.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
False start called on Ben Wrather, 3rd-and-17 incoming.

NU has found itself in some tough third down situations recently.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On the replay of second-down, Sullivan scrambles and almost get back to the original LOS.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
More hurry-up.

'Cats pick up three on first down. Porter gets nowhere on second, but Charlie Mangieri gets called for a holding penalty.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard's front gets to Sullivan again, this time for a loss of 10. 

An unsportsmanlike penalty on a Bison's defender negates the sack and earns NU a first. Phew.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan tries a pass on first-down, and it's no good.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern is moving faster than my fingers can type.

Back-to-back runs from Cam Porter, which lead to a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern takes over at their own 33 after the punt.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams sails a deep shot over his receiver, and the Bison's punt team comes on.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Williams' pass falls incomplete and was a few inches too high to be intercepted by an NU defender. 

3rd-and-10 on the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: No gain for Wheeler on first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Howard picks up nine on third down, which is more than enough for a first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams passes it short to Wheeler on second down, and the RB fumbles (but recovers). Ball has been on the ground a lot 10 minutes into action.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams hands it off on first down, and Ian Wheeler picks up two.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Student section is still filling in and has about eight more rows to fill. 

Braun will be pleased

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Renner's punt lands around the Bison's 25-yard line. The returner dropped it, but Howard holds on.

Special teams has been on it today.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Pocket collapses FAST on third, and Sullivan is smashed by Howard defenders. NU will punt.

Offense has lost its steam the last two drives after the opening TD.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
After gaining five on first down, Sullivan loses the progress on an impromptu scramble.

3rd-and-long coming up.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
An awkward punt-kickoff sequence that included a re-kick ends in NU getting the ball at the 33. 

Braun elected for the re-kick after a penalty on Howard, even though the 'Cats originally would've gotten the ball near midfield.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
'CATS GET THE SAFETY.

Pass rush swarms Williams in the endzone, and the Howard QB tries to throw it away but is called for intentional grounding.

9-0, NU!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Williams takes it himself and picks up two, forcing a 3rd-and-5.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bison gain three on a run up the middle. Give themselves some breathing room.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HUNTER RENNER MASTERCLASS. 

The senior drops it on the Howard three-yard line!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan throws his first incompletion on third down, and Northwestern will punt.

Ironic that the team's first bad sequence comes after being gifted great field position.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
'Cats pick up three on second down. 

Third-and-way long coming up.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan botches a handoff to Porter and fumbles. Barely recovers. 

2nd-and-18 on the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard's punter shanks it for a 15-yard boot. 

'Cats will take over at the Bison's 41. Couldn't ask for a better start if you're David Braun.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
NU comes up with a clutch third-down stop! 

Bryce Gallagher was in coverage on a short pass attempt from Williams.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On second down, the Bison are stuffed at the line. Third-and-short coming up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Quinton Williams also nabs a completion on his first attempt of the day. Howard advances seven yards.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Howard's returner is gobbled up by Evan Smith.

The Bison will start their first drive from their own 19.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern's first drive in review:

- 75 yards
- 2 minutes, 9 seconds
- Sullivan scrambled twice for 42 yards and a TD + completed both of his pass attempts
- NU picked up three first downs

Not too shabby.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
TOUCHDOWN 'CATS!

Sullivan scrambles on second down and turns what looked like a short gain into a 35-yard TD.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan is forced out of the pocket and scrambles for seven.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Another completion for Sullivan, this time to Bryce Kirtz — moves the chains again.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brendan Sullivan's first pass of the day is a completion to Calvin Johnson II, which he takes for a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Howard's kickoff is a short one and puts NU at the 25-yard line to start the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: All you need to know to follow along, as Northwestern takes on Howard.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern will receive the opening kickoff.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chris Collins is in attendance for today’s game. Electric.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Editors are on the scene  

(Bradley and Iggy, who???)

Name: Inside NU
Content: Every prediction has the ‘Cats scoring over 27 points, which could bode well.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern finds itself in an uncommon role as the favorite against Howard and with an opportunity to move to .500 on the season.

Name: Inside NU
Content: You can dominate the nation’s No. 3 team, but you can never beat the NW allegations

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern field hockey’s relentless pressure dominated No. 3 Iowa — the country’s best offense — from start to finish in a 2-0 win.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: No. 2 Northwestern 2, No. 3 Iowa 0 
That's 12 in a row. Longest NU win streak since 1990. The NCAA is in big, big trouble.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Green card for Greta Hinke, and Iowa will have a one-player advantage the rest of the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Really great play from Katie Jones to prevent a potential one-on-one for Iowa on the other end.

Name: Inside NU
Content: It's been reversed. No goal for Iowa after NU's video referral is successful. 'Cats are still up two.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
It's not over. Iowa's Annika Herbine strikes it in from way out, and it bounces past Skubisz, but it may have hit a Hawkeye's foot. It's under review.

If it holds, Northwestern would lead 2-1 with 2:33 to go.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Some nice stick work from Iowa to get a clean look on Skubisz, but she kicks it away. Under three minutes to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wadas' shot is saved. That's 10 corners and 11 shots on goal for NU. 5:40 to play, and it's all but over in Iowa City.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Finally, Iowa draws a corner, and she knocks away the Hawkeyes' first two shots on goal of the afternoon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Annabel Skubisz through 51 minutes

Name: Inside NU
Content: WADAS JUST DOUBLED THE SCORE! A clean look for her finds the net, and the way this one's going... it could be wraps with 11:30 to play.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
We're through three. Northwestern leads 1-0.

Through 45 minutes, the Wildcats have held the best offense in the country to:
- 1 shot
- 0 shots on goal
- 0 corners

This is without Maja Zivojnovic, by the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wadas gets a green card after tapping the ball following the free hit call.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Magnotta stops Lane Herbert's shot. Northwestern is still generating pressure -- and successfully -- even though it's up.

Name: Inside NU
Content: This is gonna be Northwestern's eighth(!) corner. Iowa still doesn't have a shot on goal through 39 minutes.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A green card on Iowa's Jacey Wittel with about seven minutes left in the third. That's the first for either team.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Down one, Iowa is starting to press. The leading offense in the country just cannot get anything going though.

Name: Inside NU
Content: NORTHWESTERN GOAL! It's Ilse Tromp off the corner feed from Alia Marshall, and NU is up 1-0!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern immediately works its way into the circle, and will draw another corner.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Second half is underway.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
HALF: NU 0, Iowa 0
Shots on goal: NU 5, Iowa 0
Corners: NU 5, Iowa 0

Only a matter of time.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Iowa finally finds its way into the circle, but a really nice play from Skubisz to knock it over the net. That'll wrap up the first half.

Name: Inside NU
Content: ANOTHER corner for NU. That's five.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Wadas's shot on the second is saved, but the 'Cats maintain possession. NU really dominating possession with its press.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Two straight corners for NU, giving them four on the day.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Olivia Bent-Cole ALMOST had a goal by taking away a free hit deep in Iowa territory! She can't convert on a one-on-one with Magnotta, though. Tough one.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
END OF FIRST: No. 2 Northwestern 0, No. 3 Iowa 0
NU got its offense going in the back half of the quarter. 'Cats lead in shots 5-1, and have three shots on goal to Iowa's 0.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Olivia Bent-Cole flips the field, has a slick feed to Chloe Relford, but Iowa snuffs it out. Really good look for Northwestern, which now has three shots on goal.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Alia Marshall gets two shots off, but Iowa goalie Mia Magnotta saves both. Both relatively contested looks.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A ton of action in the midfield right now. No shots on goal through nine minutes, with a few moments of pressure from each team.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ella Kokinis comes in for Halsey with about nine minutes to go in the first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: They're off at Iowa!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Starting for the 'Cats: Lauren Wadas, Olivia Bent-Cole, Peyton Halsey, Ilse Tromp, Greta Hinke, Chloe Relford, Katie Jones, Lauren Hunter, Alia Marshall, Lindsey Frank, Annabel Skubisz

Name: Inside NU
Content:
There is a top-three(!!) regular season matchup to start in under five minutes. No. 2  heads to Iowa City to take on the No. 3 Hawkeyes in a rematch of the thrilling 2022 NCAA Quarterfinal.

It’s on BTN. We’ll tweet it + have written coverage at the end. Tune in!

Name: Inside NU
Content: dives into Ben Bryant’s Penn State film. Spoiler alert: he got pummeled. A lot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Big Ten football schedule structure for the next couple of years dropped yesterday, and there’s a ton to take away for Northwestern.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Northwestern men’s basketball made its second-ever NCAA Tournament appearance not even seven months ago. Yet, the Wildcats are looking ahead — not at the past.

“We can talk about it at the reunions when that [2022-23] team comes back,” Chris Collins said.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern golf thrived last weekend across the board.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On the sixth episode of Pound the Talk, ,  and  talk about what they want to see from Northwestern against Howard in a more favorable homecoming matchup.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern basketball is varying its look in advance of a must-see 2023-24 season, and keeping some fan-favorites.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Content that  would be proud of.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Another All-American on this loaded of a team might just be unfair.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Pat Fitzgerald has filed a wrongful termination lawsuit against Northwestern after he was fired in July over accusations of hazing inside the football program.

Fitzgerald, who had $42 million left on his contract, was fired for cause.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
If you haven't learned already, news comes in tidal waves around here...

No USC or UCLA here. NU will go to Washington, though. That's Michigan, Ohio State and the Huskies in one year. Yeesh. This thread also contains the 2025 through 2028 schedule formats as well.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins said his dream basketball venue is Augusta National Golf Course, by the way.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on what he's excited about most: "All you really want is, can you get the best out of the guys you have? Can you become the best that that team is able to become? That's kind of what's fun for me in coaching. Can we put the best team together?"

Name: Inside NU
Content: More: "You just hope that you have a strong base of leaders. You need a little luck, too."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on if he saw last year coming: "I think you notice those qualities. I don't think people realize how hard winning is at this level. There's a lot of good players everywhere. I don't think you can say, 'Man, we're gonna win.'"

Noted competitiveness as a good indicator.

Name: Inside NU
Content: "You have to adjust and be flexible to the times. College basketball is not what it was 20 years ago. There's things we might not like as coaches at times, but we have to adjust. You have to try to stay true to your standards and your morals...but also be on the cutting-edge."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on recruiting: "We've been faced now with a number of rule changes. The NIL piece has been great for the student-athletes. We're all in support of that. When you add the element of the instant one-time transfer rule, it's made answering questions a little bit different."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Collins on his transfer additions: "We have three graduate students. Everyone else has class," he joked.

Said they're "really excited" about Ryan Langborg and Blake Preston, who bring "winning qualities."

"Winning is really hard."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins: "With each year...it doesn't make it the same. Everybody who's coming back is different. You're adding new personalities, new roles. You've got to start over. I think that's the biggest thing that all winning programs do. You can't take those things for granted."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Collins on last year's experience: "I think last year was a lot of fun for all of us. To see a group of guys rally together, and not accept that to be the reality. They were a tough group. They got confidence along the way. You can't put a price on chemistry."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Chris Collins now at the podium with other Chicago MBB coaches.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown on realignment: "You just through it. You just kind of take what's next. Just put your head down and grind."

Referenced the additions of Maryland and Rutgers in 2014.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown shouts out Chris Collins' dance moves for the dance moves at his daughter's wedding.

Now, we need to see McKeown's moves!

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown called the trip to Spain a "great experience."

Called Crystal Wang a "great player" and said Caroline Lau is a "great point guard."

"I just think we're going to be a lot better, a lot more poised. It was great for us."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
McKeown said he and NU have been "lucky" to not really have to use the transfer portal.

"We've been able to develop the Veronica Burtons to a first-round pick. I think the player development for us is really important. We like what we're doing."

Praised Tangela Smith's work.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Joe McKeown on what he took from last year: "Not much. It's my 40th year as a head coach. I think we've only had two losing seasons. They stick. We have a chip on our shoulder."

Said he was "encouraged" by late-season play and the young talent on the team.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Boo Buie and Ryan Langborg, noted TikTok sensations

Name: Inside NU
Content: A weekend of highs and lows, but full of resilience:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Here at the Chicagoland Media Tipoff, where Northwestern men's and women's basketball coaches and players will be making appearances. Stay tuned for updates!

Content: As some ex-Cats make their way back from injuries, other former NU players are stepping up:

Content: A loss that inspires? NUFB might be on the come up:

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Inside NU spoke with Northwestern AD Derrick Gragg, marking his fourth interview since July 7 — the first with student media.

Below are Gragg’s comments on decisions he made this summer, David Braun, renovating The J, the new ticket system and much more.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Abandon all hope, ye Michigan teams who enter here.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Following a win against Minnesota and a better-than-expected performance against Penn State, here’s how Northwestern can move to .500 on Saturday.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Thank goodness divisions are gone after this season.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ahead of this weekend’s homecoming matchup, Northwestern’s interim head coach David Braun met with the media on Monday afternoon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: How often does a seventh-place Big Ten team get one of the best recruiting classes in the entire conference?

Name: Inside NU
Content: On Penn State's fake kneel play near the end of the fourth quarter: "Great scheme, great execution by them. I'll never take exception to that. At the end of the day, we're there to compete."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun said he anticipates cornerback Theran Johnson to be back against Howard on Saturday.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on limiting Howard's offense: "They find ways to use tempo to their advantage. They're balanced, they do a nice job up front. You turn on that Eastern Michigan film, and there's some explosive plays in the pass game. 

"When they put the pedal down, they can get you reeling

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on his film-watching approach: "You find balance. You tip your hat to a well-rounded team, but you need to be solution-focused.

"Great coaching is identifying what our guys can do consistently while evaluating how we can improve."

Name: Inside NU
Content: He also said that the opportunity for Northwestern to play an HBCU is "historic."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the Howard marching band: "I think it's awesome. College football at its best. You talk about the student experience, fans and alumni... it's incredible. 

"To see what college athletics can do for the experience of a young person, I think it's awesome."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on what he sees for the trajectory of the team: "We've talked about how we're in the third game of our second quarter, well-timed bye right at halftime. We go 1-0 this week, we go into halftime 3-3, and we have the goals this group is striving for right in front of us."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on concerns with the rushing attack: "I think it ties back into balanced attack, complementary football, playing with a lead.

"When we can find ways to control the clock, run the football, Coach Bajakian has the entire playsheet available, we play our brand of football."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On rotating kickoff roles: "Part of it is who's got the hot foot. Part of it is splitting the load. Location of where we're putting the ball. 

"With some of the explosive qualities that Penn St. possessed on special teams, we thought Luke [Akers] would be a weapon on kickoffs."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Carmine Bastone: "He embodies so many of the qualities that make Northwestern great. Toughness, academic excellence, perseverance, great teammate.

"I think it speaks to what we want to continue to build here. We want to bring and recruit high-character young men."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Sullivan and the QB room: "The interception and the throw is a choice he'd like to have back. But unequivocally, I've spoken to the quality of that room. The depth and the leadership that exists with Brendan, what Ryan Hilinski and Jack Lausch bring."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on whether he's reflected: "An opportunity to reflect? No, probably not. But there is a great deal of gratitude from both Kristin and I for the support. For our players, for the people we're doing this with. Pretty neat."

Said they felt tangible support from NUFB alums.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On Howard: "I promise you in these walls there's no mention of FCS about our opponent. Our guys will be ready to go."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on maintaining focus against Howard: "I challenged the group after Minnesota, an emotional high's hard to come off sometimes. I thought they did a good job.

"Now they're coming off an emotional low."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on whether there's a Ben Bryant's injury update: "Not specifically. That dude is tough, he'll do everything in his power back to full health."  

If Bryant were not able to play, Braun noted that he would expect Brendan Sullivan to be the starter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "There are people that'll pat you on the back to say, 'Hey, great first half,' but we prepared to win a football game."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "There's plenty of positives to pull from, but at the end of the day our guys expected victory, expected to beat Penn State."

Said that the locker room was really disappointed with the way NU closed the game out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun's weekly press conference to start in just a few minutes. Stay tuned for tweets here!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Everything you need to know about the upcoming women’s swimming and diving season.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The ‘Cats are about to hit the homestretch.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Some figures on Northwestern’s season thus far:

10: Number of matches unbeaten
6: How many games it’s played and won in the all-gray kits
2: How many times Jackson Weyman kissed the Northwestern “N” on his jersey following the ‘Cats win at Maryland

Name: Inside NU
Content: Roman Wilson took a soul this weekend with his first quarter touchdown snag, and he may have just taken the lead for one of college football’s most prestigious awards as well.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The final score may not show it, but there were lots of positive takeaways from Northwestern’s 28-point loss to Penn State

Name: Inside NU
Content:
The Cardiac ‘Cats strike again!!

For a second straight year, NU has upset a ranked Boilermakers squad.

Name: Inside NU
Content: “Under Braun’s leadership, the Wildcats have displayed stretches of real defensive aptitude, the ability to hang around in games, an aggressive mindset and, maybe most critically, trust that Northwestern can compete with anyone,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: That ends today's pressers.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Hagarty on halftime messaging: "I think the one thing we've been preaching these last few weeks is belief. At the end of the day, our backs are against the wall. They have been for a while."

Said that the faith is "still there."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on the versatility of the receiver room: "We have so much depth in our receiver room. I think that that's honestly really good for our team. It's made us as receivers better. It gives the quarterbacks and ourselves a lot of confidence that we can go hard every play."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on Brendan Sullivan: "I've gotten to work with Sully since we first got here. He's been a guy that's taken charge. He's been a great leader for our team, even when he hadn't been the No. 1 quarterback. There was no flinch for us."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hagarty on playing well against PSU: "Ultimately, at the end of the day, it's disappointing to not get a team win. Obviously, we're going to try to put our best attributes on the field no matter what."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on Ben Bryant: "Haven't had a chance to talk with him. I think that Ben did a good job of being tough, standing in the pocket, making plays under duress, making plays with his feet."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Hagarty said that the early fumble "sparked a lot of momentum."

"We've got to continue that momentum, offensively."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hagarty on run defense: "Obviously, we just trust in ourselves. That's the main thing that we've been in doing. Breaking our backs for each other, essentially. Going 110%, never giving up. Knowing that you've got troops and cavalry coming."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson on succeeding against PSU's secondary: "I think that's sort of what I came here for. I think that we had a good gameplan, and that the offense did a good job of executing. The coaches put me in a good spot to show what I can do. Would've much rather have had a team win."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Cam Johnson and Richie Hagarty now at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the receiver room: "I just love to watch these guys work and compete. The consistency they show in practice. Awfully proud of that group. It's not a surprise."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the offensive run game: "Part of that's just balance. Part of that's finding ways to stay the course, stay patient, even if we're down by seven or 10. Heck of a job last week by our team, but even against Minnesota, we've got to find ways to play with a lead."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on James Franklin's quietude quote: "Do we know when Penn State returns to Evanston? I saw a student section that started to show up. I saw a group of energized fans. I saw a football program that's trending in the right direction. Lot of awesome stuff to get behind."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on run defense: "I think so much of it comes back to playing with a knock-back mentality. Establishing the line of scrimmage. Finish every play unblocked. That is being physical, playing with violent hands, getting off of blocks. You have to destruct blocks."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on special teams: "That's what Northwestern football is all about. Especially considering the situation with our roster right now, every single player on our roster plays an absolutely critical role. We don't need four-star, five-star guys running down on kickoffs."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the second half: "At the end of the day, everyone's going to look at this game, and look at who Penn State is. No one on the outside expected us to win this football game, for many reasons. We expected to."

Said the first half showed "what we're capable of."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Also called PSU's RBs a "talented, talented group."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on PSU players who stood out: "Specifically, just with my lens, at their offense, were the quarterback. His arm talent. His consistency. Being able to push the ball to the field, number one. His decision-making. His ability to extend some plays with his feet."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the offensive line: "We'll take a look at the tape. I thought that group made enormous strides last week against Minnesota."

Noted PSU's structure and aggressiveness.

"The best thing you can do with an opponent like that is stay in the game."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on playing better in the first half: "I challenged that defensive line in a positive manner. I think we're starting to have an understanding of what we can be as a defensive line group. We need that group to continue to mature, develop and be a huge factor."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "We needed to take calculated risks to elongate drives."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "All we chase after is right in front of us."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on decision making: "The expectation was trying to win the football game."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "Very disappointed in the result, but proud of our effort."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Interim head coach David Braun set to speak to the media shortly.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern’s defense definitely played better than expected, at least.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats’ second-half heroics couldn’t proliferate against the No. 6 team in the country.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
FINAL: No. 6 Penn State 41, Northwestern 13

The Nittany Lions outscored the Wildcats 31-3 in the second half, courtesy of short fields and better offensive play. Meanwhile, NU gained only 175 yards and was 5-for-15 on third down, ending the team's perfect home record.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan escapes for two on first, but there's been consistent penetration in the backfield for PSU all day.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Make it two touchdowns for Potts, this one of the receiving variety. Beau Pribula finds the streaking running back down the middle after a ball fake.

41-13 Nittany Lions.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan throws it right to Daequan Hardy, who runs all the way down to the Northwestern 30.

That'll do it in this one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan scrambles for a first down. Impressive run for the junior.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kirtz called for pass interference on a deep try, but Franklin declines the penalty. Now third-and-17.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Zuriah Fisher blasts Sullivan for the sixth (!) PSU sack of the day.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan hits Johnson for a first down. Under four minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Offside called on Amin Vanover makes it second-and-five.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Sullivan rolls right and has to throw it away again.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Singleton bulldozes his way in for six.

Make it 34-13 Penn State with 4:07 left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar runs but is stopped by Hagarty at the Northwestern one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton gets the carry on third and has enough for a first. Five minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar rolls right and winds Warren left wide open, who then picks up additional yardage by cutting it inside. PSU at the Northwestern seven with a third-and-three upcoming.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar drops it off to Theo Johnson, who's wrestled down by two Wildcats. Will make it second-and-18.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A solid Allar run is negated by a hold on Sal Wormley.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar finds Liam Clifford on an out route to pick up a first down. Nice design from Mike Yurcich.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton collides with Azema to bring up third-and-seven from the Northwestern 21.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar throws deep incomplete on first.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lambert-Smith sits in the Northwestern zone and gets 14 on third down. Eight minutes and counting here.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton collects only two on second, bringing up third-and-eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar loads DEEP to Cephas, but the transfer can't haul in a gorgeous throw. Would've been a touchdown.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Renner's punt goes out at the Northwestern 40.

That's a 22-yard punt.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Sullivan drops the snap, and the Wildcats will have to punt.

Can't have a three-and-out in that position if you want to come back and win.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Ben Bryant is questionable to return with an upper-body injury, per Northwestern Athletics.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun calls his first timeout of the half to avoid a delay of game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: With more white jerseys chasing him down, Sullivan has to escape and throw it away. Now third-and-nine.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Facing heavy pressure, Sullivan finds Joseph Himon II for a gain of one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brendan Sullivan is in the game for Northwestern at QB. The junior will need to make something happen with just over 10 minutes and a 14-point hole.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Henning makes a fair catch at the 16.

Northwestern trailing 27-13 with 10:28 left. Do the 'Cats have another rally in their bones?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Tight coverage by Garnett Hollis Jr. against Cephas, which will make Franklin trot out the punting team.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Hubbard tracks down Singleton, which forces a third-and-eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Allar is off trying to find Cephas on a comeback. Tough throw across the field for the sophomore.

Also, interesting that PSU is continuing to throw up by two scores with under 11.5 minutes left.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar rolls out and finds Lambert-Smith for a gain of 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Akers' kickoff is returned by Daequan Hardy to the 20.

Name: Inside NU
Content: And yes, this author did not agree with that call.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Olsen's good from 27, cutting the deficit to 14.

Also, Olsen has yet to miss a kick. That's always nice.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Jack Olsen and the kicking unit coming on with NU facing a fourth-and-10 from the 10.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant now walking off the field with assistance.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern runs a fake, but Bryant is destroyed by Curtis Jacobs. The quarterback is down and in pain.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant finds Duke Olges for two. Northwestern at the one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On a sprintout, Bryant finds Kirtz, who's knocked out by Johnny Dixon at the three-yard line.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson catches a screen and stays on his feet, getting Northwestern to the PSU eight. Pick-up of 12, and a first down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter makes a Nittany Lion miss before being tossed out of bounds. Gain of eight.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
End of the third: No. 6 Penn State 27, Northwestern 10

The Wildcats scored 21 straight in the fourth quarter last week. Are we in for another magical finish at Ryan Field?

Name: Inside NU
Content: Thomas Gordon hurdles a defender down to the Penn State 28, which ends the third quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant is nearly intercepted by Cam Miller, as the sixth-year had to throw under duress.

But, an unsportsmanlike conduct penalty on Miller gives NU 15 free yards.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Johnson up and walking off with trainers.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Despite heavy Nittany Lion pressure, Bryant throws complete to Johnson for a first down.

However, the receiver is down.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant scampers and is down at the 29, bringing up third-and-six. Inside a minute left in the third.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant looks deep to Porter, but the RB can't come up with it. Good coverage from Tyler Eldson.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Penn State's kick is a touchback.

Effectively do-or-die time for Northwestern's offense, which has mustered 83 yards and 10 points.

Name: Inside NU
Content: We'll always have this

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Allar finds Singleton wide open on a great design and ball fake.

It's 27-10 Nittany Lions with 1:24 left in the third.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton evades multiple 'Cats but is just shy of the line, at the two.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Potts follows good blocking up the middle to move the chains. Penn State inside the five and controlling the clock.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Potts fights his way for four, making it third-and-four from the Northwestern nine. Aidan Hubbard in on the tackle.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On first down, Singleton gets to the Wildcats' 12. Now the fifth catch for the start sophomore tailback.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton chugs up the left sideline as Devin Turner saves a score. Penn State on the verge of another touchdown after a 16-yard trot.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Singleton falls forward to the Northwestern 31 after a gain of three.

Content: Bryant finds Johnson open across the middle on second, getting 19! Will make it third-and-two for the 'Cats. Best offensive play of the day so far.

Content: Per Northwestern Athletics, Sean McLaughlin is "available" to return. Saw him on punt coverage, so a good sign.

Content: Renner punts to the Nittany Lion 44, where PSU will get the ball back. Good work to get that one off despite heavy pressure.

Content: Bryant gets dropped by Kobe King on first down. The Wildcats were in empty against one of the best fronts in the country.

Content:
Henning fair catches the ball at the Northwestern 18, where the Wildcats will start.

The Northwestern student section, which has definitely filled up, just started an "overrated" chant. Maybe not the best idea?

Content: Allar's pass is off the hands of KeAndre Lambert-Smith, who looked like he would've been short of the sticks anyway. PSU will punt.

Content: Carmine Bastone with a strong play to stop Singleton on second. Now third-and-three for the Nittany Lions.

Content: Allar drops it off to Singleton for six on first down. PSU at its own 41.

Name: Inside NU
Content: On third down, Allar sneaks for a first down. A little Big Ten tush push, if you will.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Allar finds Dante Cephus, but a good tackle by Adeyi brings up third-and-one.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Not surprising, but Ore Adeyi gets the start with Theran Johnson out.

Name: Inside NU
Content: McLaughlin up and walking off gingerly.

Content: Sean McLaughlin down for the Wildcats. Would be a brutal blow to a thin defensive line that needs to stop an unreal PSU offense.

Content: Nick Singleton runs for three yards on first down.

Content: Luke Akers kicking off for Northwestern, booting the ball deep for a touchback. Of note, Olsen squibbed it for the 'Cats to start the game.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern is the first team to have a lead on Penn State this year

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Olsen's kick is GOOD.

Northwestern leads Penn State 3-0 with 12:47 to go in the first.

If you had the Wildcats leading PSU *at all* today, please go buy a lottery ticket.

Content: Bryant finds Henning for a loss of two, with Daequan Hardy flying in to make the stop. Jack Olsen on to kick from the 14.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A.J. Henning called for a false start. Will make it third-and-12 from the PSU 13.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Cam Porter gets the rock on second down, picking up four. Third-and-seven for the 'Cats, with Zane Durant making the stop for the Nittany Lions.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant's first throw is complete to Thomas Gordon for a loss of one. Wildcats at the PSU 12.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That's Penn State's first turnover of the year, by the way. Unreal.

Content:
Jack Olsen kicks off, and Nick Singleton FUMBLES the ball! The Wildcats are at the Penn State 10!

Would estimate around 80% Penn State fans in attendance. A whole lot of blue and white.

Content: Duke Olges announced as the starting tight end for Northwestern, for what it's worth.

Content: The Nittany Lions roll into Evanston for the first time since 2017.

Content: Wildcats will break out the black jersey for the first time in 2023

Content: Back to unanimity.

Content:
Maja Zivojnovic in her last two matches:

12 shots on goal, 5 goals, 120 minutes. Not much else to say other than wow.

Name: Inside NU
Content: “The best solution is the easiest one. Empower fans who want to cheer on any given day, and stop keeping seats at games hostage,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: With nearly 400 yards and four touchdowns, Ben Bryant was dominant on Saturday night. takes a look at what made the gunslinger so effective.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Brian Bennett of  gives some insight on what it’s looking like for PSU out east.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Can’t get enough discussion of Northwestern’s overtime win against Minnesota? Neither can we. and  break down how the tide changed last Saturday night, and preview what might be in store for this week against No. 6 Penn State.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Just a few weeks in, the ‘Cats are showing some brilliant flashes that they could put together.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Your eyes do not deceive you. That is SIXTY FIVE boxes of pizza at the tailgate for the  game. 

Also known as a normal day’s lunch for

Name: Inside NU
Content: The firepower is coming from everywhere.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats are still unblemished at home so far this year. Before ushering in No. 6 Penn State, read some tongue-in-cheek theories about why NU has succeeded at Ryan Field.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The Wildcats dropped their first two conference games of the year against top competition.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Against a vaunted Penn State team on both sides, the Wildcats will need their offense — and belief — to shine through if they want to down the No. 6 Nittany Lions.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern stock: way up

Name: Inside NU
Content: “In a game that felt gone, in a season that already felt lost, the Wildcats weren’t ready to throw in the towel. All of a sudden, a team that looked dead in the water came roaring back to life,” writes

Name: Inside NU
Content: Plenty of ‘Cats saw pro action last weekend, and a few made a meaningful impact:

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern’s wild fourth-quarter comeback was truly a team effort, as displayed by these 10 plays that left their mark on the outcome.

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun met with the media as the ‘Cats get ready to take on No. 6 Penn State in Evanston.

Name: Inside NU
Content: After achieving a surprising comeback against Minnesota, Northwestern will face its toughest match yet, and maybe of the season, in Penn State.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The New York Jets' savior is none other than Touchdown Trevor.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Just gift-wrap trophy No. 9 already

Name: Inside NU
Content: That concludes today's presser.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the linebacker rotation: "We're really excited both those guys [Mueller and Uihlein] are playing right now. Plan on utilizing both those guys, and both their skillsets."

Said that Mueller was "playing fast" and came up with "big-time plays" in the fourth quarter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on if he's talked to other NU HCs: "There hasn't been a ton of time to spend with the other head coaches, other than all head coaches meeting here and there. I have been just incredibly impressed with not only the quality of coaches within this program, but the...people."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Said there's a "strong connection" between Penn State's offensive production and the talent it has.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on utilizing last year's PSU tape: "You certainly take a look at it. There's a lot of opportunities just to see how they attack certain fronts, certain coverages, certain alignments. The conditions certainly played a huge role in that game."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "If that's what's meant to be in the long run, that's an honor and a privilege. That's not what we're concerned with right now."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on if he's had discussions about losing the interim tag: "There hasn't been. As I've said before, I think it can be a very easy distraction, or trap, to fall into, to allow your mind to wander."

Posited that he and his wife were "put in this role for a reason."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on ball control moving forward: "It sounds really cliche, but so much of it comes back to some of the urgency and edge. It all starts at the line of scrimmage. If you want to consistently produce in that area, you better be the most physical team on the field."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Said that Coco Azema plays with a "different tempo and speed."

Also praised Jaheem Joseph's stop.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on his safeties' tackling: "It's been fun to see. Obviously, there's been times that the safeties here have been very involved in run fits prior to my arrival. Little different than it has been in the past. Those guys have really stepped up."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Penn State's defense: "They're aggressive. They're balanced. You can't find a weakness on that defense. Really well-coached. Willing to play tight coverage. Mix in some different looks. Put stress on you on first and second down."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Bryce Kirtz's consistency and confidence: "I think it goes both ways. Especially at the wide receiver position, both those things can be hard to come by. His production was no surprise to us."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on gameday adjustments from support staff: "It's been a transition directly from our team hotel, directly to Ryan Field."

Mentioned using the "atrium area" into the more traditional locker room.

"They [players] were looking for a new rhythm at home."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on his fourth-down decision to start the game: "Punting that ball no matter what. Felt like, the way that Minnesota operates offensively, that it could really be a game where possessions were limited. Felt very confident in the decision."

Name: Inside NU
Content: More: "On both sides of the football, we need to find some of that mojo in the first quarter to get going. I think that only helps an offense turn positive plays into positive drives and points."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on playing better in the first half: "I think there needs to continue to be focus on consistent execution. That drive stalls out. Two drives later, you're back in rhythm, negative play, that drive stalls out. Some of it comes back to complementary football."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Added that sometimes that desire can interfere with the ability to "cut it loose" when on the field, and that Braun has helped extract that fire within players.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the team's passion: "There's no doubt in my mind that that is within our young men, and burns at a very high level. What I would say is, this group is such a high-character, quality young men that want to do right. They want to do what they're being coached to do."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Noted that the time with family and players after the win was really critical.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on reflecting since Saturday: "The outpouring of support has been really neat. Everywhere from alumni, former players, parents of current players, mentors, people that I've coached with, high school buddies, the list goes on and on."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Bryant's injury: "I think it's just part of playing quarterback at this level. Back in the facility today."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun added that Ben Bryant started to "put things on full display" based on what the team had seen in fall camp.

Said that the offense is "gelling."

"I think we saw a group around Ben that was fully supporting him."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the offensive adjustments: "In the first half, there were a lot of self-inflicted wounds through penalties. There were moments where we were really moving the ball in the first half."

Mentioned an "explosive passing game" in the second half, plus running well.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "We have one heck of a football team coming in here. Very well-coached."

Praised James Franklin for "coaching in all three phases of the game."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun stressed the "resiliency" and "grittiness" about the Minnesota game, calling it the "expectation" and "what this program's all about."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun in his opening statement: "Excited to be back in our routine. The team was back this morning to review the Minnesota game. What a great opportunity to clean some things up, and identify areas where we need to continue to improve, while also celebrating."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Some frenetic finishes around the conference.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Interim head coach David Braun set to speak to the media any moment. Updates to follow!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Some bumps along the road.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern football is fun again and that is a total revelation.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern’s goal differential during the streak so far is 28-6 (four of those wins coming over ranked teams)!!

Name: Inside NU
Content: “Ultimately, the difficulty of that comeback paled in comparison to the challenges Braun faced this summer. Above all, it’s indicative of the head coach’s resilience, both on the gridiron and off of it,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up today's pressers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kirtz on the student section: "I really do appreciate you guys. It definitely means a lot to the team. Keep coming for sure."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Azema on this win: "It's the best win because it's the last win. This is exactly what you want to play ball for. It's nice."

Emphasized that the team will enjoy the victory but then turn the page.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kirtz on his first touchdown: "They were all huddling around me. It also just changed the energy of our sideline. Really just being able to bring that energy to the team was big for me."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Azema: "We know we're high-character men. We can't pay attention to the noise. That's all we have to do. We can't change opinions on us. We can just change how people [look at] us based on how we play."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kirtz on the offense scoring to end: "We just got to go get another one. There's no other option."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Azema on the team's identity going forward: "It's a never-give up mentality. Especially when you're down 31-10."

"We've been through hell all summer, with workouts and everything that happened. A quarter of the season's done, but it's an identity to go forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Azema: "I just feel like Coach Braun's a great guy overall. He's always been there. People want to go to war and fight for that guy."

Talked about how he lost his brother, and how Braun was there to support him.

"It's never wavering. I want to go fight for somebody like that."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Kirtz on the long road to today: "These are the guys, we put all the work in. We all make each other better. To go out there and execute as a team, based on the work we put in together, it's really rewarding."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Azema on third-down stops: "We preach all the time, field goals won't beat us."

Noted faith in the offense scoring.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Azema: "It goes back to finding our edge. We kept pushing and got it done."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant and Mangieri are done. Azema and Kirtz now at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on his relationship with Kirtz: "I love him. It's just the start for him, and I'm just really happy for him."

Name: Inside NU
Content: On Mangieri's message to the team during the game: "We've been preaching it the whole week: keep your edge."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mangieri and Bryant on being in their sixth seasons and experiencing this game together: "It means a lot. We're both really resilient. It hasn't set in, but it was a big one for all of us."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant on whether he had a favorite throw: "No. I just have got to give Coach Bajakian credit. I'm happy to have him as a coach, and happy to have these guys making so many plays for me."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mangieri on anticipating the last play: "I had a good feeling the ball was coming to me.

"The ball got lost in the lights a little bit, but it was a good ball."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Bryant on the night: "It's a lot of emotions. As a team we've been through so much, and it's so nice to get a victory in the West.

"I'm very happy with our team and how we executed."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Bryant and Mangieri at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun is done. Bryant, Azema, Mangieri, Kirtz.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the penalties: "I don't think we were penalized enough until this game. I'll live with those.

"I'll tell you what, I don't think we were playing with enough edge in the first three games."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "So many guys said, 'Coach, we got you.'"

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun choked up when talking about the moment.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on what went through his mind on the final play to Mangieri: "A.J. Henning grabbed me. He said, 'Coach, we're going to win this football game.

"Charlie's been a big reason why this program's continued to build through July and August."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Bryce Kirtz: "Confidence and consistency. The young man believes in himself, and his teammates.

"So cool to see it pay off the way that it did tonight."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the field-storming: "It's incredible. It's what we talked about. Why do you come to Northwestern as a student-athlete, or as a student? It's Big Ten football, a world-class university, and the opportunity to experience the best of both worlds."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on defensive moments that stood out: "I think the film will tell us more about that. We were all frustrated with what happened in the first half.  "I think what you saw in the first half was clean football."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on winning in the fourth quarter: "It's what this program has embodied for a long, long time. It's a reflection on the character of this team."

Thanked the athletic department staff for "making adjustments" on gameday.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the resilience: "I kept going up and down the sideline. This is what it comes back to in terms of this team. For the first time since I've been here... they weren't flinching. 'Coach, we got this.'"

Name: Inside NU
Content: This got rewritten several times.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Ben Bryant: "Certainly very proud of Ben."

Noted that "everyone" needed to elevate play.

Stressed the "resiliency" and "toughness" from Bryant.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun noted that he tried to display more of that passion today and this week.

"I've got to set the tone for Monday moving forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on maintaining winning: "I think it all starts off with our leadership and our captains. Part of our leadership is me."

Noted that he has a gift of "patience and poise" with a "burning" passion and "competitive spirit."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "This is not just a flash in the pan. This is the result of a great week in practice."

Noted that the players were "challenged" and excelled with a "totally different level of energy" in practice.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "We challenged our group to play with urgency, to play with edge. Challenged the group at halftime to stay the course."

Noted that today was going to be a "fourth-quarter game," or "however long it takes."

"Just such a reflection of what this group really stands for."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "I don't know much of an opening statement there's going to be. Pretty speechless right now. I think what we saw tonight is a direct reflection of what this group is all about."

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun now at the podium.
