Content:
Braun on Ben Bryant: "Expectations out of Ben are for him to perform on Saturday the way he practices.

"The level of consistency that we see in practice is what we need to see in games going to forward."

Name: Inside NU
Content: "What makes Northwestern special is its world-class academics with the ability to experience Big Ten athletics. [The freshman class] will play a critical role in giving us home-field advantage for the next four years."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on speaking to the incoming first-years at Wildcat Welcome: "It would've gone off much better if I knew how to operate the mic."

"In some ways, it was very humbling to take some time with the group that is absolutely critical to the student-athlete experience."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Cam Johnson: "I think there's just a level of confidence with Cam, that's contagious. Don't hear him speak much, going over the top, but it's talking with the QB, the receivers, encouraging guys."

"He's a consistent performer in practice."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Anto Saka: "The young man can rush the passer. We don't want Anto to be satisfied being a third-down specialist, we want Anto to strive to continue to strive to be an every-down guy."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
On usage of Henning in 13 personnel: "It's something that I certainly trust that Coach Bajakian's staff is doing a good job of self-evaluating."

"What I can tell you is, football is a game of matchups, and credit to that tight end group."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Ryan Field hosting its first 2023 game with students on campus : "Honestly I don't know what to expect. But really excited to have students back, for it to be Wildcat Welcome, to have the incoming freshmen at Ryan Field with the rest of the student body."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Says that Renner will remain the starting punter.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the punting situation: "A lapse of consistency. [Hunter Renner's] been such a consistent presence. Couple punts he'd like to have back, but full faith in what he's able to do."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the tight ends and O-line vs. Duke: "I think it was not where we needed to be. But there were moments of production and process that it was exactly what we were looking for."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on practice adjustments regarding tackling: "I feel like some of those fundamentals in tackling have shown up in the positive light. Just because a few missed tackles showed up against a quality opponent, doesn't mean you have to hit the panic button."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on run defense adjustments against Minnesota: "It all starts off with our fundamentals and technique. Mentioned tackling, knowing gap coverage, and starting fast.

"Minnesota, when they're ahead, is at their best. We need to find away to get them out of their comfort zone."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on improvement: "I've seen improvement from Rutgers day in and day out." However, he also noted that "it did not show up on Saturday."

"There's no doubt in our opportunities on the road so far we have not started fast, and we have not played well."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun : "[The Minnesota game] will certainly embody what Big Ten football is all about."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "Shifting into Big Ten West football, which this group is really excited about. Returning to Ryan Field against a very, very, very physical opponent that knows what it takes to win in the Big Ten West."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "Did not go down to Durham and play our best football. It's something we used as a growth opportunity this morning."

Noted that Duke's done "an exceptional job" as a program.

Name: Inside NU
Content: The game against Penn State will kick at 11 a.m. CT and will air on Big Ten Network next week.

Name: Inside NU
Content: A dangerous quarterback and plenty of positional battles...keep your eyes glued to the screen on Saturday:

Name: Inside NU
Content: If you haven’t already, it’s not too late to hop on the ‘Cats’ bandwagon.

Name: Inside NU
Content: David Braun addressed the media heading into the ‘Cats’ first game of the season versus a ranked opponent:

Name: Inside NU
Content: The NFL has to wait to see the greatness of Evan Hull

Name: Inside NU
Content: Winning handily, Northwestern escaped the utter chaos of the Big Ten West last weekend.

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up today's presser.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the run game if trailing by a lot: "Complimentary football. It takes all of us. It takes staying committed to it on the offensive side of the ball. Celebrating moving the line of scrimmage on a one-yard gain."

Noted that the team "needs to stay true to its process."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on his dance moves postgame: "There's a very firm understanding with those that know me, I lack rhythm. The second understanding is I'm a high-effort guy."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the punting job: "With both young men, we're continuing to develop both."

Said that Renner and Akers have "different" skillsets, with Renner being able to focus on "operation time" and moving the pocket.

Called Akers an "absolute weapon."

Name: Inside NU
Content: On Mueller's interception, and not returning it all the way: "It was discussed on the sideline," he said with a laugh.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the defense stepping up: "Everyone will get sick of me using the two words 'complimentary football.' We believe in it."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said he was "most impressed" with the "energy, effort, the passion" that the team exuded.

"That is the expectation every week."

In terms of specific positions, mentioned the offensive line/tight ends in the run game, with Marshall Lang being Offensive Player of the Week.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on his relationship with Jeremiah Lewis: "Very good player. Very mature. Smart. Driven. We were disappointed to see him go."

But, Braun said there's "no hard feelings" with Lewis deciding to transfer during a "time of uncertainty."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Bryce Kirtz: "I think he has the ability to open some things up, to be a shot guy that can really push the ball down the field."

Mentioned his "veteran leadership" helping on the field.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun also praised Duke's weapons and offensive line.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on utilizing past tape against Duke: "It's just collecting information. Our defensive structure is different now. There's enough similarities in terms of four-down structure."

On Riley Leonard: "He just continues to get better and better. He's done a tremendous job."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on Lausch's role moving forward: "The details and specifics, I'll leave that to the offensive staff."

Said that he's told the staff that Lausch "needs to be on the field."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on early defensive struggles, with a laugh: "If you have any suggestions for me, I'm open to them."

Said the defense is "hungry" and almost expecting to be perfect.

"I think it just comes down to this group, collectively, maturing... [of] not trying to make every play."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on utilizing Henning: "It was critical. A credit to Coach Bajakian and the offensive staff for finding ways to get the ball in his hands."

Underscored Henning's versatility as creating problems for defenses.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "Saturday was a great reminder that we have a good football team."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on preparing for Duke: "I think this group is at its best when it's an underdog. We're not paying attention to lines."

Noted that 2023 will "not be linear," calling the Rutgers game a "let down" but UTEP providing an "emotional high."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun stressed that Duke is a "very well-coached" team on top of its talent.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on gameplanning for Duke: "There's a lot of crossover. There's multiple guys on that Duke staff that spent time here, that have relationships with guys on our staff. There's a little bit of a chess match going on."

Noted that there's a "tremendous amount of respect."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on playing multiple quarterbacks against Duke: "Ben Bryant is our starting quarterback. We plan for that to continue to be the case."

Added that NU is "finding ways to get Jack [Lausch] involved."

Also praised Ryan Hilinski for "coming in with poise."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Added that he's not worried about a lack of continuity with establishing five starters.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said that right tackle would be "by committee," something which was established this summer.

"In the second half, Josh came in. We were hot, and stayed with the hot hand. We'll continue to have both those guys rotate in."

Said he was "impressed" with Thompson.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on injury updates: "Not going to share any specifics."

Said they "anticipate" both Ben Bryant and Brendan Sullivan being available against Duke.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on messages that stood out from his first win: "The continued support from our parents of our players, people within the greater Northwestern community. Other head coaches. Those that have been alongside us every step of  the way."

Said Winona State teammates were there.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said that Duke is "balanced" with "high-end quarterback play."

"We have a big challenge ahead of us."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said that players had yesterday off, calling it "much-needed."

Said there were a "couple corrections" from UTEP.

"Really, really well-coached football team," he said about Duke.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Northwestern's kick against Minnesota is set for 6:30 p.m. CT. Primetime at Ryan Field in the Big Ten home opener.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Interim head coach David Braun set to speak to the media shortly. Stay tuned for updates!

Name: Inside NU
Content: Here are the key takeaways from Northwestern football’s first win of the season and first home win in almost 700 days.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Since dropping the home opener, Northwestern field hockey has been nothing but dominant.

Name: Inside NU
Content: ANGELA ZE-BACK

Name: Inside NU
Content: “At long last, that evasive sense of victory is finally associated with Northwestern football, all that matters for the next few days — and unquestionably something unifying all factions of a divided fanbase,” writes .

Name: Inside NU
Content: That wraps up today's pressers.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Saka on Braun's first win: "I'm just happy for him. Just for us to go out and get this done for him, it means the world to him, and it means the world to us."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller said that "not a lot has changed" since Braun was elevated to head coach.

"We have an awesome staff around him."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Saka said that Braun is a "players' coach."

"He's the greatest."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller on Coach Braun: "He's one of the most honest and humble people I've ever met. He's been incredible in stepping up."

Said he's been "truthful" but also supportive.

"A huge role model for me."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Saka: "You work so hard for moments like this. We put in the work during practice, and we put it out on the field."

Mueller said that Saka had terrific dance moves, too.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller on the offense scoring points: "It's a team game. It doesn't matter how good one side of the ball is if [you] can't play together."

Saka added, "Instrumental."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mueller on his interception: "Kind of zoned off. High-to-low on that play. His eyes were on him. I just jumped it."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Saka on the DL: "We build each other up. We have depth there, so we're able to rotate through guys. The older guys have been a key part of developing our younger guys."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller: "The huge emphasis was brotherhood. We know who we are. We know our character."

Saka said that outside noise became quieter when the team began preparing and coming together.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mueller: "We need 103 guys to go and win these games."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mueller on his interception: "A huge emphasis this fall camp was getting the ball out. A lot of that was working on our hands and making sure we can catch the ball."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller on the win: "We've been grinding for this moment for a while."

Saka added, "We're going to celebrate this. We're going to keep it rolling."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Mueller on third-down stops: "That was one of the first things that we talked about in defensive meetings. That's really the one thing we've got to do. It was a huge emphasis this week."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Saka on succeeding this year: "It's great. Last year, I had a lot to learn. It was great to sit behind some great players. Finally stepping up in my role now."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Mueller said that Braun emphasized "playing with passion."

Saka: "We just had to make a decision," referring to executing on the gameplan.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Anto Saka and Xander Mueller now at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lausch on the mood in the locker room: "Excited. We've put in a lot of hard work this past week to gameplan for this team."

Lausch and Porter said Brendan Flakes and Joe DeHaan had top dance moves in the locker room.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter on maintaining success: "Now, we're shifting our focus. We can't ride the highs of last week."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Porter pointed to early in the second half, specifically five-to-six-yard runs, as a turning point.

"Those start to wear on defenses."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter on outside circumstances: "We've been dealing with it for a long time now. We made a choice that we're going to come together. This is just the start."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Lausch: "Everyone's thankful to win." Also threw out the word "excited."

Porter added, "We've been through a lot. A lot of ups and downs throughout the offseason, but we stuck together. They're a good opponent."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lausch on the quarterback dynamics: "I think it's awesome. We have a great room. It's a cool way to show that we can score in a lot of different ways."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Porter on second-half changes: "We were having some early success in the first half with some different run schemes. Coach kind of came in at halftime and said we were going to pound the round."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Lausch on his role: "I knew that I would have an opportunity to get the ball a little bit. I just wanted to make the most of it. I was excited for it."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Cam Porter and Jack Lausch now at the podium.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
That'll do it for Braun's presser.

As he walked off the podium and greeted awaiting players, could hear celebrations and high fives.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on the offensive line's better play: "It's a credit to that group, credit to Coach Anderson. A credit to a commitment to the run game, with Coach Bajakian."

Said it represents the "resiliency" of the group, which "came back to work and battled their buts off."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on support: "The support, that's what we're paying attention to. We feel it. The people that were heard today were heard."

Said he wants to "invite people to be a part of this."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on his conversation with Thomas Gordon to end the game: "Just a lot of joy. A lot of gratitude."

Said he didn't know Gordon well before he became HC, but that the two have grown closer.

"Really appreciate his passion and commitment to this program."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun praised the camaraderie within the DL group.

"They push one another. They care about one another. That is a group that, if you walked in in February, you would go, 'Whew. Where do we go from here?' Now, I look at that group and go 'How good can we be?'"

Name: Inside NU
Content: "That dude was not going to be denied."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on a moment that changed momentum: "There's not a specific play that comes to mind, but you could just sense it. We were staying ahead of the sticks."

Mentioned doing well on first down, gaining three to set up shorter downs, plus Cam Porter's running.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Called Lausch a "weapon."

"It was fun to see him out there."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on the uses of Lausch and Henning: "A.J.'s just really difficult, because you don't know where he's going to line up. Do we really want to play man when he's on the field? When Jack is in the game, you better be incredibly aware, as a play-caller, what you're playing."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on Bryant's injury: "To be honest with you, I'm not sure."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "Those sacks and interceptions, it's not a coincidence that both of them showed up today."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on takeaways: "It's things we've been emphasizing since I arrived."

Praised LaMarcus Hicks.

"He's taken over our ball disruption circuit."

Mentioned playing man coverage, but also "spacing, vision, ball-out-break defense," such as on Gallagher's INT.

Name: Inside NU
Content: More: "We don't know what the long term looks like, and that's okay."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun: "I've been charged with leading this program forward. Had an opportunity to talk to a group last night. It starts off with supporting our players. It comes down to serving them; not serving my interests."

Said that "every decision" has been through that lens.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun called his wife a "rockstar" and emphasized how appreciative he was for being able to have his family in the stands.

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on when he realized his team had won: "Gratitude. Gratitude for the people that we're doing this with. Gratitude and a lot of humility for the opportunity. Soaking it all in. I know that I'm ready for this moment."

Said it "still feels surreal."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun on running the ball well: "I think it was a commitment to it. Staying with it, and utilizing all of our guys. We talked about these types of moments. We're going to win games with our fundamentals, with our technique."

Said Cam Porter "embodied" a Big Ten RB.

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on what the win means to the program: "I don't know if we needed it. What we need is just continued support, and need one another. But, my gosh does it feel good."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said he told players at the Ryan Field scrimmage that Northwestern has won by "being a great fourth-quarter team."

"There's nothing flashy about how the 'Cats are going to win."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on adjustments in the second half: "We keep talking about complimentary football. What complimentary football is, it's not flashy. It's not instant gratification. It takes time."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun on his first career win: "I'll tell you right now: this is our win. It means so much to me because it was with an incredible group of people."

Name: Inside NU
Content: Braun: "I really want to thank everyone that came out today. We've talked about in fall camp how critical it is for us to protect Ryan Field. We got off to a great start today."

Name: Inside NU
Content:
Braun said it's "no secret" that last Sunday was a disappointment, and that the staff "challenged" the players to move on.

Noted that the team was in half pads Tuesday, and that the group "continued to stay focused" in practice.

Stressed controlling process and passion.
